Full Title: 2nd Shaikh Ayaz International Conference 
Short Title: On Language & Literature 

Date: 07-Nov-2008 - 10-Nov-2008
Location: Faculty of Arts, University of Sindh, Jamshoro, Pakistan 
Contact Person: Muhammad Qasim Bughio
Meeting Email: saicll@arts.usindh.edu.pk, dean@arts.usindh.edu.pk
Web Site: http://www.saicll.usindh.edu.pk 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Meeting Description:

2nd SAICLL by falling in line with the UN mission. This year-2008 in which the
UN proclaims the current year as an 'International Year of Languages, in Effort
to Promote Unity in Diversity and Global understanding through Languages'.

As for specific conference objectives, the most will primarily spotlight in:

Exchange of ideas and information with regard to language significance and
research in the context of goodwill, peace, and closer cultural relations among
diverse ethnic group at national as well as international levels.    

Extension, improvement and refinement of languages including English language
related to the regional, national and global needs of the people.   

Enhancement of language-understanding-culture as an instrument for the promotion
of tolerant civil society. 

Discard myths, fables and stereotyped claims about languages and generate body
of information instead, based on scientific research/investigation of languages. 

Provide world linguists and scholars a common platform to exchange ideas and
explore better future prospects of language and literature development.  

To generate research addressing vital issue in Language and Literature. 

Explore the possibility of forming World Linguists Association. 

Call for Papers

We are pleased to announce that 2nd Shaikh Ayaz International Conference on
Language and Literature (SAICLL) is going to be held in Nov 7-10, 2008 falling
in line with UN mission. This year-2008 in which the UN proclaims the current
year as an ''International Year of Languages, in effort to promote Unity in
Diversity and Global understanding through Languages''.

Important Dates:
Submission of Abstract/Proposal: July 31, 2008
Announcement of Acceptance: Aug 15, 2008
Submission of Full Papers: Sep 30, 2008

1. An abstract/proposal should not exceed 500 words.
2. Name of the author, co-author (if any) showing institutional affiliation and
mailing address, email address, telephone and fax numbers be sent with abstract
/ proposal.
3. Send to: saicll@arts.usindh.edu.pk

Abstracts/Proposals of Paper/Papers are invited on the following suggested themes:

Suggested Themes for Language:
Linguistics
Sociolinguistics			
Psycholinguistics
Neurolinguistics
Historical Linguistics 			
Geoliinguistics
Applied Linguistics
Language Planning and Policy
Lexicography
Philology
Language and Politics
Languages in Contact
Endangered Languages 
Linguistics Situations of various countries around the world
Language & Technology
Other Related Themes

Suggested Themes for Literature:
World Classics
Literary Criticism
Medieval and Renaissance literature
Contemporary Literature
Comparative study of Literature 
Modern Literature
Prose (Fiction-Nonfiction)
Poetry
Drama, Film, Television and other Media
Other Related Themes

Suggested Themes for Shaikh Ayaz:
Shaikh Ayaz and his contribution towards Language, Literature, Education & Society
The Poetry of Shaikh Ayaz
Diction in the Poetry of Shaikh Ayaz
Mysticism in the Poetry of Shaikh Ayaz
Shaikh Ayaz: a Revolutionary Poet
Shaikh Ayaz: a Poet of all Times
Symbolism in the Poetry of Shaikh Ayaz
Different Perspectives of the Poetry of Shaikh Ayaz 
Shaikh Ayaz and his Contemporaries
Translations of Shaikh Ayaz's Poetry in various Languages
Prose of Shaikh Ayaz
Other Related Themes

